  "text": "The concept that biliary salts may induce AKI is not new, Haessler et al in 1922 [CITATION_1] analyzed the urine of humans and dogs with jaundice and concluded that biliary salts could be found in urine sediment and further studies showed that, as the liver injury resolves and renal function recovers, the biliary salt tends to disappear. However in the last decade only few cases reports addressed this issue [CITATION_2] .",
